    "description": {
        "de": "Examples:\n\ntype br&lt;ctrl-d&gt;: expands to' best regards'\n\ntype mfg&lt;ctrl-d&gt;: expands to 'mit freundlichen Gr√ºssen'\n\ntype de&lt;ctrl-d&gt;; expands to 'Dear best regards'.Please notice that the cursor is now after the 'Dear ', so you can continue typing in the middle of the replacement text.\n\nThe replacement can be multiline:\n'Dear #c, \n\nbest regards, \n&lt;yourname&gt;'\n\nDefine your own shortcuts. Insert #c where you want the cursor to be displayed.\n\nHTML or markdown styling will come in an update.\n\n\nNotice: I noticed that the TB tools-&gt;addons page sometimes does not show the menu with the three dots, which has the settings. If you close the tab and reopen via tools-&gt; addons, then the addon submenues come back (happens in my 78.8.0 for all addons that are installed)."
    },
